HEADWORD: Biliary
<hw>Bil"ia*ry</hw> <pr>(b⟦icr⟧l"y⟦adot⟧*r⟦ycr⟧; 106)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>bilis</ets> bile: cf. F. <ets>biliaire</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Relating or belonging to bile; conveying
bile; <as>as, <ex>biliary</ex> acids; <ex>biliary</ex>
ducts</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Biliary calculus</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a
gallstone, or a concretion formed in the gall bladder or its
duct.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

